# ConflictResolver Agent Implementation

Build the third agent in the PulseAI pipeline. It reads `ingestion.json` and `insights.json`, finds source pairs that disagree on the same metric, resolves them or flags for human review, and writes `contradictions.json`.

**Critical rule**: Never force a resolution when sources are equal. If a conflict involves a discarded source, flag for human review.

## Signal Scores (from actual ingestion output)

| src_id | File | Cred | Recency | Discarded |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| src-1 | analytics_by_region.json | 0.90 | 1.0 | No |
| src-2 | marketing_spend.json | 0.85 | 1.0 | No |
| src-3 | monthly_regional_sales.pdf | 0.85 | 0.667 | No |
| src-4 | news_competitor_expansion.html | 0.80 | 0.722 | No |
| src-5 | news_pricing_blog.html | 0.30 | 1.0 | **Yes** |
| src-6 | pos_ecom_last_30d.csv | 0.95 | 1.0 | No |
| src-7 | social_post_spam.json | 0.00 | 1.0 | **Yes** |
| src-8 | support_tickets.jsonl | 0.60 | 1.0 | No |

## Three Pairs to Detect

| Pair | Signal A | Signal B | Metric | Classification | Expected outcome |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **C1** | src-3 (PDF, +5% YoY) | src-6 (CSV, ~-25%) | `growth_pct_lahore` | direct_conflict | **resolved** → CSV wins via recency (Δ=0.333≥0.3) |
| **—** | src-2 (marketing spend) | src-1 (analytics reach) | `campaign_health_lahore` | different_angle | **not_a_conflict** (both facts are true) |
| **C3** | src-4 (news, 30% cheaper) | src-5 (blog, "roughly similar") | `competitor_pricing_claim` | direct_conflict | **needs_human_review** (involves discarded source) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `find_metric_pairs` operates on **all** signals (including discarded) so it can detect the pricing contradiction. The `decide()` function adds a pre-rule: if either signal is discarded → `needs_human_review` with reason `"involves_discarded_source"`. This ensures we never silently swallow a contradiction just because one source was filtered out.

