### Resolver (pure Python decision rules)

#### [NEW] [resolver.py](file:///c:/Users/baisa/Desktop/pulse-ai/agents/conflict/resolver.py)

- `score_source_pair(sig_a, sig_b)` — returns `{recency_delta, credibility_delta}`.
- `decide(sig_a, sig_b)` — decision rules in order:
  1. If either signal is discarded → `needs_human_review`, reason `"involves_discarded_source"`
  2. If `abs(recency_delta) >= 0.3` → pick more recent, reason `"recency"`
  3. If `abs(credibility_delta) >= 0.2` → pick more credible, reason `"credibility"`
  4. Else → `needs_human_review`, reason `"equal_sources"`

